Topic
Cloud Functions 2nd Gen — HTTP trigger, deployment, invoker pattern, and project migration due to missing default infrastructure.Objective
Deploy a private HTTP-triggered Cloud Function, understand the relationship between Cloud Functions and Cloud Run, and test access with an identity token.Key Concepts

Cloud Functions 2nd Gen runs on Cloud Run under the hood — every function deployment creates a Cloud Run revision
Cloud Run = full containerised service; Cloud Functions = single-purpose code triggered by HTTP or events
requirements.txt tells GCP what libraries to install before running your code
--entry-point tells GCP which specific function in your code to call
--trigger-http = HTTP triggered; alternative is event triggers (Pub/Sub, Storage etc.)
--source=. = deploy from current directory
--gen2 = 2nd Generation runtime (built on Cloud Run)
2nd Gen functions need roles/run.invoker on the underlying Cloud Run service — roles/cloudfunctions.invoker alone is not enough
Default Compute SA is created automatically when Compute Engine is first used — missing SA causes Cloud Functions build failures
Identity tokens expire after 1 hour — no manual cleanup needed
Cloud Functions charges per invocation + compute time
